   
    User Management API Documentation
1. API Overview
The User Management API provides endpoints for user authentication and user data retrieval. The API follows RESTful principles and returns structured JSON responses for both success and error scenarios.
Standard Success Response

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Operation completed successfully.",
  "data": {}
}


Standard Error Response

{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Error description.",
  "error_code": "ERROR_IDENTIFIER",
  "timestamp": "2026-02-28T10:30:00Z"
}


2. Base URL
https://api.example.com/v1
3. Authentication
The API uses JWT Bearer Token Authentication. After successful login, include the token in the request header:
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
4.1 Authenticate User
Method: POST
URL: /auth/login
Authenticates a user using email and password credentials. If valid, a JWT access token is returned.
Request Body
email (string, required) – Registered user email
password (string, required) – User account password
Sample Request

{
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPassword@123"
}


Sample Success Response (200)

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "User authenticated successfully.",
  "data": {
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "token_type": "Bearer",
    "expires_in": 3600
  }
}


Sample Error Response (401)

{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Invalid email or password.",
  "error_code": "AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS",
  "timestamp": "2026-02-28T10:30:00Z"
}


4.2 Retrieve Users
Method: GET
URL: /users
Retrieves a list of registered users. Requires authentication.
Sample Success Response (200)

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Users retrieved successfully.",
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "johndoe@example.com",
      "role": "admin"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "name": "Jane Smith",
      "email": "janesmith@example.com",
      "role": "user"
    }
  ]
}


Sample Error Response (401)

{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Unauthorized access.",
  "error_code": "AUTH_UNAUTHORIZED",
  "timestamp": "2026-02-28T10:35:00Z"
}


5. Error Codes
400 – INVALID_REQUEST – Request validation failed
401 – AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS – Incorrect login details
401 – AUTH_UNAUTHORIZED – Missing or invalid token
500 – INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR – Unexpected server error
